### Frontend Manual Verification (Browser)
1. Start dev server: `cd d:\haykhathon\campusride-frontend && npm run dev`
2. Navigate to `/login` → form renders, email validation works
3. Navigate to `/register` → all dropdowns populate, regex blocks invalid emails
4. Login with valid user → redirected to `/dashboard`, JWT stored
5. `/rides/search` → map loads, geolocation or click works, results show match scores
6. `/rides/create` → map click sets points, form submits
7. `/rides/:id` → two-way acceptance buttons appear correctly for rider vs passenger
8. `/trip/:id` → live marker moves on WebSocket, chat bubble opens, messages send/receive, auto-scroll works, read receipts update
9. `/admin` → only accessible with ADMIN role; table loads, verify/block actions work; map shows active rides
